diff --git a/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md b/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
--- a/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
+++ b/docs/ANTIMALWARE_0.1.1.md
@@ -55,6 +55,12 @@ Active intelligence is stored at `/security/zenovguard-intelligence.zmid`; its m
 
 The active object is written before its version state. Boot reconciles a newer valid signed object with older version metadata, while an active object older than persistent state is rejected.
 
+An update first retains the previous signed database in the existing supervisor-only scan workspace and validates the complete candidate. Before the candidate can replace the active object, ZenovGuard commits a durable `INTELLIGENCE-UPDATE` authorization record containing the candidate digest and size. Only then may the active policy be written, read back and revalidated, followed by version state, metadata synchronization and in-memory activation.
+
+This ordering closes the power-loss window in which a new signed object could previously become the boot-reconciled active database without any persistent update evidence. A crash before the authorization record leaves the old policy. A crash after the authorization record but before policy replacement leaves a harmless recorded intent. A crash after replacement leaves both the candidate digest evidence and a signed candidate that boot can reconcile.
+
+Live policy-write, read-back, version or sync failures restore the previous database and version and synchronize the rollback. Rollback failure leaves ZMID unavailable and the wider enforcement path fail-closed. An audit-append failure occurs before policy mutation and therefore needs no policy rollback.
+
 ## Prevention boundary
